Class MyQueue<E>

java.lang.Object
implementations.MyQueue<E>
Type Parameters:
E - the type of elements stored in the queue
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, QueueADT<E>
public class MyQueue<E> extends Object implements QueueADT<E>, Serializable
MyQueue is an implementation of the QueueADT interface that uses a dynamic doubly linked list (MyDLL) to store elements. It follows the First-In-First-Out (FIFO) principle and supports standard queue operations.

    • search

      public int search(E toFind)
      Description copied from interface: QueueADT
      Returns the 1-based position where an object is on this queue. If the object o occurs as an item in this queue, this method returns the distance from the front of the queue of the occurrence nearest the front of the queue; the first item on the stack is considered to be at distance 1. The equals method is used to compare o to the items in this queue.
      Specified by:
      search in interface QueueADT<E>
      Parameters:
      toFind - the desired object.
      Returns:
      the 1-based position from the top of the queue where the object is located; the return value -1 indicates that the object is not on the queue.
